        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer6845194" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer9959354308533431532">I didn&apos;t really get this book when I first read it, but having read it multiple time since, it&apos;s become like a bible. Rand outlines her Objectivist philosophy and explains the concept of <i>rational self-interest</i>. This book will turn you into an asshole once you read it, someone will smack you, you&apos;ll read it again, pick up the part everyone misses (about morality being intrinsic, not non-existent) and then you&apos;ll live a happier, more whimsical life. </span>
  <span id="freeText9959354308533431532" style="display:none">I didn't really get this book when I first read it, but having read it multiple time since, it's become like a bible. Rand outlines her Objectivist philosophy and explains the concept of <i>rational self-interest</i>. This book will turn you into an asshole once you read it, someone will smack you, you'll read it again, pick up the part everyone misses (about morality being intrinsic, not non-existent) and then you'll live a happier, more whimsical life. </span>
