        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer4006627295" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer18219051783807649485">If I had read The Virtue of Selfishness; shortly after being utterly galvanized by Mien Kampf written by Adolf Hitler, during the early stages of BLM as an avid member of BSU(yes the Black Student Union.. just in case promoting Adolf&apos;s book threw off your initial opinion about my prior political beliefs), before I nearly sold my soul to the angry mob &quot;Vox Populi&quot;, etc etc I don&apos;t think I could have finished a single page of this book without feeling immorally obligated to set it ablaze in a mass</span>
  <span id="freeText18219051783807649485" style="display:none">If I had read The Virtue of Selfishness; shortly after being utterly galvanized by Mien Kampf written by Adolf Hitler, during the early stages of BLM as an avid member of BSU(yes the Black Student Union.. just in case promoting Adolf's book threw off your initial opinion about my prior political beliefs), before I nearly sold my soul to the angry mob "Vox Populi", etc etc I don't think I could have finished a single page of this book without feeling immorally obligated to set it ablaze in a mass book burning, followed by amputating both of my hands for even opening it in the first place.<br /><br />"ETC" is the shorthand version of et cetera, which is used at the end of a list to indicate that further, similar items are included. I felt it necessary to define etc, not because I think other people don't understand what it means, but rather to emphasize that I believe this seemingly unrelated list of events in my life are fundamentally related. The fundamental belief that relates them is that We matters more than me, or you, or I, or any rational conscious sensible individual with a single solitary soul. Plural's vs Singular's. As if We's weren't made up of Me's? AssszzZZzzZZzz efff! Plural's weren't made up of Singular's? The truth is they aren't, there is no unity of units in this community(just commies), and there are no unique beautiful snowflakes in Project Mayhem, because the very moment that Me dedicates his life to WE... Me dies. And that death would be a romanticized Fight-Club'esque typa death. Something like:"In project mayhem we have no names but in death we do... His name was Isaac Velazquez, HIS NAME WAS ISAAC VELAZQUEZ, HIS NAME WAS ISAAC VELAZQUEZ, HIS NAME WAS ISAAC VELAZQUEZ, HIS NAME WAS ISAAC VELAZQUEZ, HIS NAME WAS ISAAC VELAZQUEZ, HIS NAME WAS ISAAC VELAZQUEZ, HIS NAME WAS ISAAC VELAZQUEZ, HIS NAME WAS ISAAC VELAZQUEZ, HIS NAME WAS ISAAC VELAZQUEZ, HIS NAME WAS ISAAC VELAZQUEZ, HIS NA